<p>If, say, you wanna build a backstage system for your RoR website, and want a page to display some server system info just like phpinfo() function in PHP.</p>

<p>Well, then the following pre-defined Constants of Ruby would be useful</p>
<code>
RUBY_PLATFORM<br />
RUBY_VERSION<br />
RUBY_RELEASE_DATE
</code>
<p>Nextly, some rails pre-defined values</p>
<code>
ENV['RAILS_ENV'] # or Rails.env<br />
ENV['RAILS_RELATIVE_URL_ROOT']<br />
ENV["RAILS_ASSET_ID"]<br />
ENV["RAILS_CACHE_ID"]<br />
ENV["RAILS_APP_VERSION"]
</code>


<p>Want to get the current database adapter programatically?</p>

<code>
ActiveRecord::Base.configurations["development"]["adapter"]
</code>

<p>And the I18n setting:</p>
<code>
I18n.locale
</code>

<p>Now how about some Rails config value that was stored in config/environment.rb ,etc? I haven't quite figured it out yet. I'll update this page when it's done.</p>
